('Urs Lienhard', 'Urs', 'Lienhard', 'Regional Hotel General Manager in Thailand | Exploring Gracious Culture | Follow for reflections on leading and living with greater heart.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/urslienhard', 'urslienhard', $${"about": "🌍 My work has taken me across three continents, from on-the-ground hotel leadership to corporate environments, where I have been involved in projects, pre-openings, and rebrandings.📈 Along the way, I have worked closely with owners and organisations to ensure alignment between vision, performance, and long-term value. \n⠀\n✨🧑‍🤝‍🧑A large part of my journey has been centred around people — developing talent, building teams, and creating environments where individuals can grow and create memorable guest experiences. Over time, this led me to reflect more deeply on what truly shapes meaningful experiences, in hospitality and in life.\n⠀\n✨ I describe it as Gracious Culture.\n⠀\n🧡 At its heart, it is a simple choice: to make life more enjoyable for ourselves and those around us.In a world increasingly shaped by technology and AI, I believe the human element becomes even more important.\n⠀\n🇹🇭 Shaped by Thai traditions, Buddhist reflections, cultural values, and nearly two decades in hospitality, my work explores nine qualities of gracious living. It is both reflective and practical, drawing on everyday moments and timeless lessons from Thailand on how to live and lead with greater heart.\n⠀\n✅ They are for anyone who believes that gentleness is not weakness. For those who seek beauty not only in places, but in people. Whether in leadership, business, service, or daily life, the intention remains the same: to create more human, thoughtful, and gracious ways of working, leading and living.", "addressCountryOnly": "Thailand", "addressWithCountry": "Krabi, Thailand", "addressWithoutCountry": "Krabi", "backgroundPic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5616AQFMTI7qmbtxjg/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/B56Z0U9CMa