k & front office of this department operational according to schedule. As a result, the Hotel started receiving the first online bookings by November ’19. \nSab is a very independent lady who has positive attitude. She always has a forward-thinking attitude and is able to anticipate\n", "recommendations/1/name": "Sabariah Awis", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Brand Strategist", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sabariah-awis-41398b155/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAACVXkI8BgaKAoG0l4vKryh-TEOQXS6531JY", "recommendations/2/context": "Hugo worked with Fredrik but they were at different companies", "recommendations/2/date": "September 24, 2016", "recommendations/2/description": "I have had both the opportunity and pleasure of working with Fredrik, while I was COO at Katara Hospitality and Fredrik was Director of Asset Management at Qatari Diar,   both companies under the umbrella of Qatar Holding.   During our tenure at these respective companies we concluded some amazing asset deals in Europe.\n\nThroughout that time, Fredrik proved to be a passionate and people-orientated professional with excellent knowledge in hotel operations both back and front.  Highly methodical in his approach and most importantly, Fredrik business and financial acumen are second to none and so are his negotiation skills, he appreciates both the fine details and the bigger picture of a project.  It was a great pleasure working with Fredrik on these projects / asset acquisitions, renovations and conversions. \n", "recommendations/2/name": "Fredrik Jonsson, MRICS, HAMA", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Hospitality & Real Estate Investment Executive | Founder & Managing Partner – Mereha Group | Sovereign Wealth Platforms | Mixed-Use & Destination Developments | Board Director", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonssonfred/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAKfnIBMmUuA4J4zKCMfNnm9MZEwr0wFzA", "recommendations/3/context"